blog.name: squeefangrrlproject
blog.title: The Squee! Project
blog.description:
The Squee Project explores topics of womanhood, feminism, representation, creativity and production, body image, race, sexuality and more. As fangrrl creators, we attempt to cover the full fandom experience including cosplay, conventions, comic books, movies, podcasts, fanfic, episodics, and creating spaces for women, girls and femmes to collaborate and network in geek-nerd culture. 
We create short form video interviews, aca-fandom editorials, con coverage, unboxing, book, tv, and film reviews and long form documentary episodes. Our pilot episode "Identifying As A Fangirl" has won 4 awards and screened at dozens of conventions and film festivals. We also present panels on women and fandom at conventions.

blog.description: Holistic Writer / INTJ / Chaotic Good / Slytherin / Jewish / QIA-spec in LGBTQIA+ / autistic rabblerouser / still in my 30s / they-pronouns. Emma Goldman stan. Survivor of traumas I only discuss when relevant. Contains black tea, insomnia, poetry, & fic—but mostly just fic. If you're looking for CoT 'Verse and the rest of my Good Omens fic, you can find it here. As of 2013, all of my old LJ-era fanfiction has been uploaded to AO3. I'm the nutter behind @ask-agnes-nutter, so feel free to send asks. I moderate for the largest, most active GO Discord server, The Ritz; if you would like an invite, please DM me. You can pester me; I strongly encourage anons, because I know not everyone finds sending asks easy. If you want to know where to find my published work, email me on irisbleufic@gmail.com or send a DM. If you make art based on my writing, podfic my stories, or do anything you want me to see, tag it #irisbleufic. I won’t tell folks they shouldn't follow, but there's complex content here. I tag thoroughly. You can ko-fi me if you wish.

summary: am i hallucinating or did u mention having a discord server for folks more anxious than excited about the go tv adaptation? i...
question: am i hallucinating or did u mention having a discord server for folks more anxious than excited about the go tv adaptation? i might want in ...
answer:
Nope, anon, you aren’t hallucinating. I did indeed briefly post an invite link, although I thought better of it when I realized randos with bad intentions might stumble in.

So far, Bookshop Back Room (we are a predictable bunch of neurodivergent nerds, what can you do) has ten or so people in it, and it vacillates amiably back and forth between anxiety / humorous frustration about known aspects of the upcoming show, discussion of book canon and fanfiction, and a ridiculous amount of just plain talking about books and media. It’s about a week old, and the baseline rules are 1) give trigger warnings, 2) don’t toss out spoilers for anything unless we determine everyone’s on the same page or doesn’t mind being spoiled, 3) no being there solely to lurk, and 4) don’t be a dick.

If this sounds appealing to you, either send me a PM while signed into Tumblr or email me on irisbleufic@gmail.com, and I’ll send you an invite link!

calicovirus said: “no lurking” damn, that’s me out lmao

Thanks for giving me reason to clarify this, @calicovirus, and the reasoning behind it.  There are a few members of the chat whose anxiety ratchets up greatly if there are people on the server who legitimately never contribute at all.  They feel monitored, in a sense.  So far, about half are much quieter than the other half, but that is not what’s considered lurking.  We mean no joining and never saying anything.  So if you think you’d blip into the discussion even occasionally, I’d say drop me a message, and I’ll send you the invite.

(No rule-system is perfect, but, as the moderator, I’m taking majority concerns as seriously as I can, and those have been almost zero.  This is a hang-out space where, hopefully, folks won’t feel judged for not being 100% enthusiastic 100% of the time.)
